rts-err-1: RTS Threshold setting range is 1~2347. Please check the settings again.
ipfilter-info: IP filtering restricts access from a connected device by blocking it's IP address.
macfilter-info: Mac filtering restricts access from a connected device by blocking it's mac address.
portfilter-info: Port filtering restricts incoming and outgoing service ports on a connected device.
firewall-info: The SPI (Stateful Packet Inspection) firewall safeguards against cyberattacks and verifies the traffic passing through the router based on the protocol. This feature comes pre-enabled.
parentalcontrol-info: Parental control is a functionality that empowers you to limit an individual's online activities and access. It enables you to block and filter content based on specific days and times.
ipfilter-name: Check whether the character consists only of the alphabet A~Z and numbers 0~9 and is blank.
ipfilter-direction: Check whether a direction for the rule has been selected.
ipfilter-source-ip: Check if it is blank or not, check for IP format.
ipfilter-source-port: Make sure that only numbers, entered from port 0 to 65535. “-“ can be used for port range.
ipfilter-destination-ip: If the Source IP is not blank, check whether the Destination IP is blank or not, check the IP format.
ipfilter-destination-port: Make sure that only numbers, entered from port 0 to 65535. “-“ can be used for port range.
ipfilter-protocol: Make sure you have selected the Protocol for the rule.
macfilter-name: Check whether the character consists only of the alphabet A~Z and numbers 0~9 and is blank.
macfilter-mac-address: Check whether blank or not, and MAC format.
portfilter-name: Check whether the character consists only of the alphabet A~Z and numbers 0~9 and is blank.
portfilter-port-or-range: Make sure that only numbers, entered from port 0 to 65535. “-“ can be used for port range.
portfilter-protocol: Make sure you have selected the Protocol for the rule.
level-info: DoS (Denial of Service) Protection shields the LAN from DoS attacks by preventing the network from being inundated with excessive requests. It offers the flexibility to filter three types of attacks to suit your specific requirements
low-rule: Low: Provides minimal protection with minimal impact on router performance.
medium-rule: Medium: Offers moderate protection with a somewhat noticeable impact on router performance.
high-rule: High: Delivers high-level protection but has a noticeable impact on router performance.
dos-protection-info: DoS Protection safeguards the router against ICMP-Flood, UDP Flood, and TCP-SYN-Flood attacks. You can set the thresholds to activate the corresponding protection measures.
icmp-info: Input a value between 5 and 3600 to activate ICMP-Flood protection immediately when the number of ICMP packets surpasses the predefined threshold.
tcp-info: Input a value between 5 and 3600 to activate TCP-SYN-Flood protection immediately when the number of TCP-SYN packets surpasses the predefined threshold.
udp-info: Input a value between 5 and 3600 to activate UDP-Flood protection immediately when the number of UDP packets surpasses the predefined threshold.
init-password: There is no initial samba password. It needs to be set up.
wifi-only-same: The Wi-Fi password is set to default. We recommend that you change your password.
web-only-same: The WEB UI password is set to default. We recommend that you change your password.
config-restore-fail: It is not a Static IP backup file. Please check the backup file again.
ntp-server-check: NTP server format is incorrect. Please check again.
url-check: The URL format is incorrect. Please check again.
are-you-sure-to-mode-reset: Are you sure to mode reset?
are-you-sure-to-changed-session: If you change the WEB session timeout, the session timeout value will be the same for all users.
